    },
    {
      "para_id": "p1",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 1,
      "text": "The very term \"sideloading\" is a brazen attempt by massive tech corporations to delegitimize the act of running \"unapproved\" software on computers, phones, tablets, and other devices that we purchase and own. Would you say that when you install Vivaldi or TIDAL on your Windows PC you are \"sideloading\"? Of course not.",
      "char_len": 318,
      "chunk_word_count": 52,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9550561797752809,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.839622641509434
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9662921348314608,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p2",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 2,
      "text": "Running our own software; no matter what it is or where we obtain it is not up for debate and must be codified as a basic consumer right.",
      "char_len": 137,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9818181818181818,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8029197080291971
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6808080808080809,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p3",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 3,
      "text": "For example:",
      "char_len": 12,
      "chunk_word_count": 2,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9090909090909091,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.9166666666666666
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.3818181818181818,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p4",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 4,
      "text": "A BitTorrent client is explicitly and harshly disallowed by Apple despite having completely legal uses, even on alternative app stores, in direct defiance of the spirit of the EU's Digital Markets Act.",
      "char_len": 201,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9764705882352941,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.845771144278607
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7379084967320262,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p5",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 5,
      "text": "Video-game emulators have been banned by Google, Apple, and others.",
      "char_len": 67,
      "chunk_word_count": 10,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9310344827586207,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8656716417910447
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.3982758620689655,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p6",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 6,
      "text": "A simple \"Hello, world!\" program I compile myself cannot be distributed without first becoming a \"verified\" Apple developer and paying an annual fee; Google is moving Android in the same direction.",
      "char_len": 197,
      "chunk_word_count": 31,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9520958083832335,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8477157360406091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7043496340652029,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "A pornography VOD app cannot be distributed on Apple devices, and the same obstacle exists on Google-controlled Android.",
      "char_len": 120,
      "chunk_word_count": 18,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.970873786407767,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8583333333333333
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5198220064724919,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "Bespoke or alternative operating systems - freely available Linux distributions, for instance - are almost always blocked by deliberate hardware incompatibilities, missing drivers, secret documentation, and closed-source firmware.",
      "char_len": 230,
      "chunk_word_count": 26,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9605911330049262,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8826086956521739
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6343322386425836,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "These examples barely scratch the surface of what is impossible or unnecessarily difficult to do with hardware we own, solely because vendors insist on defining how we use it. The manufacturer should have zero say in whether I run a BitTorrent client, an emulator, or my own kernel.",
      "char_len": 282,
      "chunk_word_count": 48,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9787234042553191,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8333333333333334
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9840425531914894,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "I should not have to \"notarize\" my apps or \"prove\" myself worthy to run unsigned code on the device I bought. Companies should not demand personal data from developers merely to grant the \"privilege\" of executing code on our own machines. A vendor's refusal to endorse an application does not entitle it to dictate how I use my property, nor to act as a morality or legality police force.",
      "char_len": 388,
      "chunk_word_count": 69,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.965625,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8247422680412371
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.97421875,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "The internet and multimedia landscape are deteriorating rapidly because a handful of giant technology firms have made normal anti-competitive, anti-consumer practices that directly harm culture, creativity, art, and consumer rights.",
      "char_len": 232,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9655172413793104,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.875
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6991379310344827,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "Imagine for a moment that desktop PCs worked the same way. What incentive would Microsoft have to approve LibreOffice - a German open-source suite that competes with Office? Why notarize it at all? And why not pressure motherboard vendors to introduce firmware \"quirks\" so Windows cannot realistically be replaced? We avoid that dystopia only because decades of norms and expectations keep the PC ecosystem comparatively open.",
      "char_len": 426,
      "chunk_word_count": 65,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9750692520775623,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8474178403755869
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9813019390581719,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p13",
      "section_id": "s0",
      "section_path": [],
      "ordinal": 13,
      "text": "There is no principled difference between a phone, a tablet, a smart-watch, and a traditional computer. Size and polish do not nullify general-purpose computing, and yet vendors purposefully hide it. Enforcing these restrictions takes vastly more engineering effort than simply allowing \"unapproved\" binaries to run.",
      "char_len": 316,
      "chunk_word_count": 45,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9595588235294118,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8607594936708861
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9238357843137255,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    }
